                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">No. 101.</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Pringle</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1885-11-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 28, 1885</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 307.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received Mr. Hall’s dispatch of September
                    29 last, No. 427, relative to the plottings of ex-President Soto against the
                    peace of Honduras and the part taken in the same by the British steamer Dorian,
                    through the assistance of Messrs. A. D. Straus &amp; Co., of New York.</p>
                <p>I have inclosed a copy of Mr. Hall’s dispatch to the Attorney-General and have
                    observed that it might be proper to instruct the district attorney at New York
                    City in regard to the alleged operations of Messrs. A. D. Straus &amp; Co., to
                    the end that in case they were infringing the neutrality laws of this Government
                    all necessary steps could be taken in the premises.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>T. F. BAYARD.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
